WEBVTT

00:01.235 --> 00:02.167
<i>Amy: Previously on "heartland":</i>

00:02.169 --> 00:03.368
Lisa: We just heard
on the radio that

00:03.371 --> 00:06.304
There's been another break-in.
- How many's that been?

00:06.340 --> 00:08.440
- The source of the break-ins
is pretty obvious.

00:08.442 --> 00:10.109
<i> It's that horse therapy centre</i>

00:10.111 --> 00:12.878
<i> And those juvenile delinquents</i>
<i> it's bringing in.</i>

00:13.013 --> 00:14.312
- So, that's what it's about,
hey?

00:14.382 --> 00:16.314
Your soft spot for locked-up
animals? Just like your dad.

00:16.384 --> 00:18.851
(thudding blow)
- (crashes to table)

00:18.853 --> 00:20.252
- What's this?
I haven't seen that before.

00:20.321 --> 00:22.387
- It's just a piece of metal.

00:22.423 --> 00:24.022
- Okay,
and you'll set the alarm?

00:24.025 --> 00:25.757
- Yes, I'll set the alarm.

00:25.793 --> 00:28.260
Lisa: Jack, stop! Stop! Stop!
Jack: Stay here. Stay here!

00:28.395 --> 00:30.062
- What if they're still
in there.

00:30.197 --> 00:32.464
- That's what I'm hopin'.
(remi whimpers)

00:32.599 --> 00:34.199
Anybody in here?

00:34.268 --> 00:35.834
♪♪♪

00:39.206 --> 00:41.106
(police radio chatter)

00:42.743 --> 00:45.210
<i>Lisa: Honestly, it's, it's hard</i>
<i> to say what all was stolen.</i>

00:45.212 --> 00:47.946
<i> Um, or if it was just thrown</i>
<i> around, but definitely,</i>

00:47.948 --> 00:49.882
The big-ticket items:
The stereo,

00:49.884 --> 00:52.217
And the television. Um--

00:52.286 --> 00:54.553
- Lisa, was your laptop
out on the table?

00:54.622 --> 00:56.555
- Yes, I think it was.
- It's gone, too.

00:56.624 --> 00:58.223
- So, my computer.

00:58.225 --> 00:59.925
- I notice you also have
a pretty high-tech

01:00.060 --> 01:02.394
Security system installed.
Jack: (sighs)

01:02.463 --> 01:05.230
- We do. Uh, it wasn't
working very well tonight,

01:05.266 --> 01:07.900
So we turned it off.
Unfortunately.

01:07.902 --> 01:09.434
- I see.

01:09.437 --> 01:12.971
- Uh, dad's all-around cowboy
trophy is missing.

01:13.040 --> 01:14.439
- (sighs)

01:14.508 --> 01:16.708
- Oh, and the box
with your watch in it.

01:16.744 --> 01:18.110
- It doesn't matter.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.045
- It had all your cufflinks,
honey.

01:20.047 --> 01:21.813
- Lise, really,
it's not worth reporting.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.517
- We'll let you know
if anything turns up.

01:25.519 --> 01:27.386
It's a shame about that
security system.

01:27.521 --> 01:29.721
Would've been nice to catch
these guys on camera.

01:29.723 --> 01:31.523
Sorry about this, folks.

01:31.525 --> 01:33.325
- Thanks.
- Take care.

01:33.394 --> 01:35.327
- Thank you, we appreciate it.

01:35.329 --> 01:37.129
(footsteps recede,
door opens then shuts)

01:38.532 --> 01:40.132
(light footsteps approach)

01:42.002 --> 01:44.069
- Amy, no, no, the kids.

01:44.071 --> 01:46.004
- They can't wait in the truck
all night, grandpa.

01:46.006 --> 01:48.006
It's past their bedtime.

01:48.008 --> 01:50.008
And besides,
everything's okay, right?

01:50.144 --> 01:51.610
We're all fine.

01:51.679 --> 01:53.578
Let's go get ready for bed.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.681
- I don't wanna be alone.

01:55.683 --> 01:57.582
- No way we're sleeping
in our rooms tonight.

01:58.786 --> 02:00.318
- (sighs)

02:01.355 --> 02:03.021
- Okay, I have an idea.

02:04.091 --> 02:05.456
(drill whirs)

02:07.495 --> 02:09.695
- (sighs)

02:09.830 --> 02:11.196
(footsteps thud)

02:13.968 --> 02:16.168
(footsteps approach,
door creaks open)

02:18.873 --> 02:20.372
- How are you doing?

02:20.441 --> 02:22.507
- I'm fine.

02:22.543 --> 02:24.442
Except for tim's stupid trophy.

02:24.478 --> 02:26.712
I'll never hear
the end of that now.

02:26.847 --> 02:28.546
- Nope, probably not.

02:29.717 --> 02:31.183
How ya doin'?

02:32.520 --> 02:35.520
- (sighs) well, if I hadn't
turned off that damn alarm,

02:35.523 --> 02:37.121
This never would've happened.

02:37.158 --> 02:39.791
- Jack, don't blame yourself.

02:39.793 --> 02:41.626
- Who else is there to blame,
lise?

02:43.030 --> 02:44.529
- It... What're you doing?

02:44.532 --> 02:45.897
Oh, honey, come--

02:47.535 --> 02:49.201
- I'm done with these.

02:49.270 --> 02:51.803
I'm going back to protecting
this ranch my way.

02:52.740 --> 02:54.406
- Whose watch was that?

02:54.408 --> 02:56.475
Why didn't you wanna report it?

02:58.479 --> 03:00.679
- It was my father's.

03:00.748 --> 03:02.814
(footsteps thud)

03:02.883 --> 03:04.283
(drill clatters on table)

03:04.418 --> 03:07.286
♪♪♪

03:08.755 --> 03:10.756
<i> Lisa: Ooh,</i>
<i> what's happening here?</i>

03:10.758 --> 03:14.059
- We're having a sleepover!
- Oh!

03:14.061 --> 03:15.560
- Well, let me help out, then.

03:17.097 --> 03:20.565
Hey, you girls, why don't
I build us all a fire?

03:21.835 --> 03:23.969
- Can we roast marshmallows?
- Oh, I will go get them.

03:24.038 --> 03:25.837
- Thank you!
Lyndy: Yes! Yes!

03:25.973 --> 03:28.106
(footsteps thud)

03:28.108 --> 03:30.275
(wood clatters,
fire crackles)

03:30.411 --> 03:37.249
♪♪♪

03:39.119 --> 03:40.585
(fire crackles)

03:40.621 --> 03:42.454
<i>Jefferson: You wanna try it on,</i>
<i> don't you?</i>

03:42.523 --> 03:45.257
- Yep. Mm-hmm.
- (chuckles)

03:45.392 --> 03:47.859
(watch jingles)

03:47.928 --> 03:54.466
♪♪♪

03:54.535 --> 03:56.435
<i> - You'll grow into it one day,</i>
<i> jack.</i>

03:58.672 --> 04:01.406
<i> You know, that watch will</i>
<i> be yours some day, you know.</i>

04:01.475 --> 04:03.742
<i> Just like this whole ranch.</i>

04:05.446 --> 04:08.647
♪♪♪

04:08.782 --> 04:10.915
(crickets chirp)

04:13.153 --> 04:15.553
(rifle clatters lightly)

04:15.589 --> 04:22.427
♪♪♪

04:25.933 --> 04:32.871
♪♪♪

04:32.940 --> 04:40.679
♪♪♪

04:40.681 --> 04:42.914
♪ and at the break of day ♪

04:42.983 --> 04:46.684
♪ you sank into your dream ♪

04:47.821 --> 04:49.521
♪ you dreamer ♪

04:49.590 --> 04:52.190
♪ oh oh oh oh ♪

04:52.259 --> 04:53.925
♪ you dreamer ♪

04:56.730 --> 05:00.365
♪ you dreamer ♪

05:05.672 --> 05:08.273
(birds chirp)

05:08.275 --> 05:10.675
<i> Lou: I just still can't</i>
<i> believe all this.</i>

05:10.711 --> 05:12.210
- I know.
- (sighs)

05:12.279 --> 05:13.545
- They were in our home.

05:13.680 --> 05:16.348
- I mean, it's just stuff,
but you feel so violated.

05:16.417 --> 05:18.149
- Yeah, well...

05:18.185 --> 05:20.619
More than that,
I'm worried about grandpa.

05:20.754 --> 05:22.220
Nobody's saying it,

05:22.289 --> 05:24.356
But he must be feeling pretty
bad about all this.

05:24.491 --> 05:26.691
- Oh, yeah.
- (footsteps approach)

05:26.760 --> 05:28.560
- Morning.
- You couldn't sleep either?

05:28.695 --> 05:30.695
- Ugh, too wound up.

05:30.764 --> 05:32.697
Jack didn't even come
to bed last night.

05:32.700 --> 05:34.199
(floorboards creak,
door shuts)

05:34.334 --> 05:35.934
- He was out
pacing on the porch.

05:38.472 --> 05:40.772
- I just wanted some air,
is all.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.940
- And you needed your rifle
for that, did ya?

05:44.244 --> 05:47.245
(footsteps thud)
- yes, I did.

05:47.314 --> 05:48.347
(footsteps recede)

05:49.516 --> 05:51.716
- Whew, well I gotta
get to work.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.452
- Yeah, um I should probably
head out now, too.

05:53.454 --> 05:55.253
I'm gonna go over to cooper's

05:55.255 --> 05:57.122
And see how they're doing
after last night.

05:57.124 --> 05:58.656
Thank you so much
for taking the girls

05:58.726 --> 06:00.992
To the fair in town. I know
that's really gonna help

06:00.994 --> 06:03.061
Keep their mind off things.
- Of course.

06:03.063 --> 06:05.997
It's the last day, and
they've been dying to go, so.

06:05.999 --> 06:07.932
Lou: Have fun, girls!
(whispers) thank you.

06:08.001 --> 06:09.868
- Have fun!
Oh, hey parker!

06:09.937 --> 06:11.669
- Hey.
- Hi, parker.

06:12.840 --> 06:14.940
(footsteps approach)
- I heard about the robbery.

06:15.075 --> 06:17.476
Everyone in town
is talking about it.

06:17.611 --> 06:19.811
- Are they? Fantastic!

06:19.880 --> 06:21.680
- Aren't you guys
completely freaked out?

06:21.815 --> 06:23.615
I mean, what did they take?

06:23.750 --> 06:26.417
- My sanity, for a start.

06:26.453 --> 06:28.019
- Mostly just made a mess.

06:28.088 --> 06:29.955
And the tv's gone,
and there's some...

06:30.090 --> 06:32.824
Heirlooms, but...
- Like what?

06:32.893 --> 06:35.226
- Well, they took
tim's rodeo trophy,

06:35.295 --> 06:38.230
And um, jack's father's
watch.

06:38.232 --> 06:40.499
- The watch doesn't matter,
lise.

06:42.035 --> 06:44.302
- Oh... Okay. Okay.

06:44.438 --> 06:47.305
Girls! Parker's here!
Let' go!

06:47.441 --> 06:54.212
♪♪♪

06:55.315 --> 06:57.248
(hooves thud)

06:57.317 --> 07:00.318
Cooper: Hey! How's it goin'?

07:00.320 --> 07:02.854
- I was about to ask you
the same thing.

07:02.989 --> 07:04.523
How ya doin' after last
night?

07:04.658 --> 07:06.992
- It'll be fine. I put some
calls out to a few people,

07:06.994 --> 07:08.726
And I'm a firm believer
that things always have a way

07:08.796 --> 07:10.928
Of working out. It has to.

07:10.964 --> 07:13.598
- Okay. But...Heartland
was broken into last night

07:13.600 --> 07:15.132
When we were at the gala.

07:15.169 --> 07:16.934
- Does that mean you're
here to search my bunk?

07:16.970 --> 07:18.402
- No.

07:18.439 --> 07:21.072
Logan, I-I'm here because
I'm gonna work with that

07:21.141 --> 07:23.141
Wild horse today,
and I thought

07:23.210 --> 07:25.610
Maybe you'd wanna join,
if it's okay with cooper?

07:25.612 --> 07:27.612
- That sounds like fun.

07:27.614 --> 07:30.715
- Yeah, I'll go get my stuff.
- Okay.

07:30.717 --> 07:33.818
♪♪♪

07:33.887 --> 07:35.887
(bench clatters)
rick: What are you doing?

07:35.956 --> 07:38.023
- Thought I had left my work
laptop here at the office

07:38.025 --> 07:40.358
Last night, but I can't...
Seem to find it.

07:40.427 --> 07:42.059
But I'm sure it's here,
somewhere.

07:42.095 --> 07:43.895
- And if you can't?

07:43.964 --> 07:45.897
- Then... It's at home.

07:46.032 --> 07:48.066
- But your home was robbed.

07:48.135 --> 07:49.634
- I know. I don't wanna
go there, okay?

07:49.703 --> 07:51.503
- Uh, well let's hope
we don't have to.

07:51.638 --> 07:53.705
There's a zillion
confidential documents,

07:53.707 --> 07:56.040
And emails on there,
and the...

07:56.109 --> 07:58.910
Lou, the budget cuts,
they, they haven't

07:58.979 --> 08:01.246
Been made public yet.
This is bad!

08:01.315 --> 08:04.115
- No, rick, we will find it.
It'll be fine.

08:04.184 --> 08:06.051
- It better be

08:06.053 --> 08:07.586
Because that laptop,
in the wrong hands,

08:07.721 --> 08:10.989
Goodbye approval rating,
and hello scandal.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.857
- (stressed exhale)

08:12.860 --> 08:15.527
Just... Help me. Okay?

08:17.664 --> 08:19.531
(the paint nickers)

08:19.600 --> 08:21.432
Hey, come on. Come on.

08:21.468 --> 08:23.334
(hooves thud)
whoa.

08:24.470 --> 08:26.237
(amy clicks her tongue
and hisses)

08:26.240 --> 08:27.806
Sh-sh-sh-sh.

08:27.941 --> 08:30.275
(gate rattles)

08:32.779 --> 08:36.281
- Okay, so now what?

08:36.350 --> 08:39.017
- Well, the first thing
we need to do

08:39.086 --> 08:41.086
Is to get him to trust us.

08:41.221 --> 08:43.655
I'm hoping that this colt
will remember shadow,

08:43.724 --> 08:45.823
And realize we don't
wanna hurt him.

08:45.859 --> 08:48.026
<i> - Why do you think he'll</i>
<i> trust shadow so much?</i>

08:48.028 --> 08:50.495
- Horses understand
other horses.

08:50.497 --> 08:53.098
And shadow came
from the same herd.

08:53.100 --> 08:54.832
So did challenge, actually.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.735
- Maybe he should've
stayed there.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.836
- Why? Challenge loves
the centre.

08:58.906 --> 09:00.905
- I know. I just hate mac
for what he did.

09:02.242 --> 09:04.842
- Yeah, but thanks to you,
he's not gonna do it again.

09:04.912 --> 09:06.544
Right?

09:06.547 --> 09:08.847
- (sighs) people like mac,

09:08.982 --> 09:11.349
I mean, they look at my dad
and they just...

09:12.886 --> 09:15.186
They just see a loser who's
been in jail for five years.

09:16.957 --> 09:18.889
You know, but I still see
my dad.

09:20.193 --> 09:21.726
He's my best friend.

09:25.065 --> 09:26.665
(sniffles)

09:26.667 --> 09:28.633
- And he's gonna be out soon,
right?

09:28.669 --> 09:30.868
- Yeah, and we're gonna
move away.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.536
You know, start fresh.

09:32.573 --> 09:34.305
My dad, he needs
a clean slate.

09:35.475 --> 09:37.541
(scoffs)

09:37.578 --> 09:39.144
Guess I do, too.

09:39.279 --> 09:43.815
♪♪♪

09:43.950 --> 09:45.783
- No, I just,
just got to the ranch.

09:46.953 --> 09:49.020
Yeah, so hurry up and get
back from new york, huh?

09:49.155 --> 09:51.156
Okay, I love you. Yep. Bye.

09:52.326 --> 09:55.559
(gravel crunches under foot,
beeps call off)

09:57.497 --> 09:58.830
(footsteps thud on porch)

10:00.467 --> 10:02.233
(latch clangs)

10:02.269 --> 10:05.837
♪♪♪

10:05.839 --> 10:08.840
(door clunks)
jack?

10:08.909 --> 10:13.444
(footsteps thud)

10:13.480 --> 10:14.812
Jack?

10:16.316 --> 10:23.254
♪♪♪

10:23.290 --> 10:29.194
♪♪♪

10:31.998 --> 10:33.831
(door creaks open)

10:35.302 --> 10:37.268
Hey, what happened?

10:37.270 --> 10:38.937
- We got robbed.

10:39.072 --> 10:40.872
- Is everybody all right?

10:41.007 --> 10:43.074
- Yes, tim, we're all fine.

10:43.209 --> 10:45.443
Your trophy's gone.

10:45.512 --> 10:47.746
- Wh--, uh gone?

10:47.748 --> 10:49.814
I go to one rodeo
and all hell breaks loose?

10:49.816 --> 10:51.416
How did this happen?

10:51.551 --> 10:52.950
- How do you think?

10:53.020 --> 10:56.154
We were out, thieves took
advantage of an empty house.

10:56.156 --> 10:58.289
- Well, lou said you had
a fancy new alarm system.

10:58.291 --> 10:59.724
- I turned it off.

11:01.428 --> 11:03.128
- (scoffs)

11:03.263 --> 11:05.630
You realize how important
that trophy was to me, right?

11:05.632 --> 11:06.831
It's irreplaceable.

11:06.833 --> 11:08.933
- Yeah, well,
if you loved it so much,

11:08.969 --> 11:10.669
Why'd you leave it
lying around my house?

11:10.804 --> 11:12.537
- I didn't leave it
lying around,

11:12.672 --> 11:14.505
I left it on display.

11:14.574 --> 11:16.174
For others to appreciate

11:16.176 --> 11:18.009
While I was travelling
with jessica.

11:18.078 --> 11:19.711
Where ya going?

11:19.780 --> 11:21.512
- To town, to get new locks.

11:22.582 --> 11:24.716
- What do you need
the locks for?

11:24.851 --> 11:27.051
Glass is broken.

11:27.120 --> 11:28.787
You need glass!

11:28.789 --> 11:31.189
<i> Amy: Hey, parker!</i>
<i> Come meet logan!</i>

11:32.559 --> 11:34.425
<i> Looks like you had</i>
<i> fun at the fair, huh?</i>

11:34.461 --> 11:37.462
- That's a nice uh...
Tiger face.

11:37.531 --> 11:40.064
- Oh, um, well...Yes.

11:40.133 --> 11:42.934
Uh, anything to please
the kids, right?

11:44.404 --> 11:46.337
Amy, I rode over to ask you
something.

11:46.339 --> 11:47.772
- Yeah, what is it?

11:47.907 --> 11:50.007
- Jack's watch,
he's upset about it.

11:50.077 --> 11:51.709
I wanna find it for him.

11:51.712 --> 11:53.110
Do you know what
it looked like?

11:53.146 --> 11:55.280
- Until it was stolen, I
didn't even know it existed.

11:55.415 --> 11:57.115
Sorry.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.283
- Okay, then.
Worth a shot.

11:59.352 --> 12:01.051
Still, I'm here now,

12:02.455 --> 12:04.421
I might as well stay.

12:04.458 --> 12:06.991
To watch you work
with this horse.

12:06.993 --> 12:08.893
- Right. The horse.

12:08.895 --> 12:11.629
♪♪♪

12:14.968 --> 12:16.667
<i> Lisa: Oh, there you are!</i>

12:16.737 --> 12:18.603
You weren't here when we
got home from the fair.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.506
- No, I was in town.
I was getting new locks.

12:21.508 --> 12:23.641
- Oh!
- Gg, I brought you this!

12:23.643 --> 12:25.643
- You did! Well, thank you!

12:26.913 --> 12:30.248
And what did you win,
a bear, too?

12:30.317 --> 12:31.950
- In the fishing game.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.585
I wanna fish for real.
Can you please teach me?

12:34.621 --> 12:36.687
- Yes, I would love

12:36.757 --> 12:38.757
To teach you to fish!

12:38.892 --> 12:41.593
I just have to finish
a couple things up here first

12:41.595 --> 12:44.562
But, you bet.

12:44.631 --> 12:46.731
- Okay.
- Okay. (chuckles)

12:46.866 --> 12:48.599
(footsteps tap away)

12:48.635 --> 12:50.769
- So, all new locks.

12:50.904 --> 12:53.304
Is that maybe a bit much,
honey?

12:53.439 --> 12:55.606
(plastic crinkles)

12:55.642 --> 12:57.608
Okay.

12:57.677 --> 12:59.477
(footsteps recede)

13:01.481 --> 13:03.480
(door slams repeatedly)

13:07.954 --> 13:10.254
(jack sighs)

13:12.793 --> 13:14.225
(water runs)

13:15.962 --> 13:17.762
(echoing whoosh)

13:17.764 --> 13:18.929
(footsteps thud)

13:20.567 --> 13:21.966
(young jack breathes shakily)

13:21.968 --> 13:24.768
(sombre music)

13:24.805 --> 13:30.741
♪♪♪

13:32.212 --> 13:33.845
(chains rattle)

13:33.980 --> 13:36.848
♪♪♪

13:36.983 --> 13:39.317
(echoey thumps)
(screen door thuds)

13:40.720 --> 13:42.820
(door shuts)

13:42.823 --> 13:45.156
♪♪♪

13:45.225 --> 13:47.725
(glass clinks,
alcohol burbles)

13:47.861 --> 13:50.461
♪♪♪

13:50.463 --> 13:52.696
It was a nice ceremony, dad.

13:54.167 --> 13:57.035
I think June would've
liked it.

13:57.037 --> 13:59.170
<i> Jefferson: June should</i>
<i> be here, jack!</i>

13:59.305 --> 14:01.005
Not in that damn box.

14:02.409 --> 14:04.609
- (sobs)

14:04.611 --> 14:06.810
It's not my fault, dad!

14:06.847 --> 14:09.213
(sobbing)

14:09.282 --> 14:11.348
<i> I wasn't even here.</i>

14:11.384 --> 14:14.018
(sobbing)

14:16.523 --> 14:23.928
♪♪♪

14:33.473 --> 14:35.506
R clunks open)

14:36.442 --> 14:37.976
(door clunks shut)

14:39.212 --> 14:42.179
(items clatter)

14:42.181 --> 14:44.115
♪♪♪

14:44.250 --> 14:46.183
I know it's here.

14:46.219 --> 14:50.455
♪♪♪

14:50.457 --> 14:52.089
(sighs)

14:53.560 --> 14:55.259
(car door clunks shut)

14:55.262 --> 14:57.528
Tim: Everybody's talking
about the robbery at maggie's

14:57.564 --> 15:00.064
And most people suspect those
kids from cooper's centre.

15:00.199 --> 15:03.034
- Yeah, well, you can thank
paula westfield for that.

15:03.036 --> 15:05.403
She made a big scene there
last night.

15:05.405 --> 15:07.071
- Well, I heard
she's not the only one.

15:07.206 --> 15:09.040
Two of those kids get
in a fight,

15:09.109 --> 15:11.008
In front of everybody?
- Yeah, this...

15:11.044 --> 15:13.711
This boy, logan,
got into it with another kid.

15:13.780 --> 15:15.179
They got kicked out.
- Kicked out.

15:15.248 --> 15:17.348
And then we got robbed.
Where'd they go?

15:17.350 --> 15:19.751
What's their alibi?
- Ah, tim, don't start.

15:19.886 --> 15:22.353
- What, I want my trophy
back, jack!

15:22.488 --> 15:24.956
Look it, if that logan kid
had something to do with it,

15:25.091 --> 15:26.824
Or any of his buddies--
- dad...

15:26.960 --> 15:28.292
- Hi.

15:28.295 --> 15:30.627
- Logan and I are staying
for dinner!

15:30.664 --> 15:32.162
(footsteps thud)

15:34.133 --> 15:35.933
- Logan?

15:37.938 --> 15:39.370
(screen door shuts)
huh.

15:42.709 --> 15:45.175
- I'm gonna change
all the locks,

15:45.211 --> 15:46.644
First thing in the morning,

15:46.779 --> 15:48.913
Including the one
in your room,

15:48.982 --> 15:50.848
The one that goes outside.

15:50.984 --> 15:53.050
- Someone can come
through my door?

15:55.522 --> 15:57.555
- No, honey,
see that's the point.

15:57.557 --> 15:59.323
Now they won't be able to.

15:59.359 --> 16:01.392
- But you're saying
they could have?

16:01.428 --> 16:04.595
- Listen, there's nothing
to worry about here.

16:05.999 --> 16:07.265
- More garlic bread, logan?

16:07.400 --> 16:09.500
- Sure. Thanks.

16:09.502 --> 16:11.135
(utensils clang gently)

16:12.205 --> 16:14.071
Amy: Hey.
- Hmm?

16:14.107 --> 16:16.807
- You've been pretty quiet.

16:16.843 --> 16:18.342
- Um... Sorry,

16:18.411 --> 16:20.077
I'm just dealing
with a bit of a crisis.

16:20.113 --> 16:23.114
I misplaced my laptop,
and if it was stolen,

16:23.116 --> 16:25.683
I'm kind of... Ruined.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.518
- I hear ya, honey.

16:27.587 --> 16:30.354
A loss like that
can ruin ya.

16:30.390 --> 16:32.023
Take my trophy,

16:32.158 --> 16:34.291
Which meant the world to me.

16:34.427 --> 16:37.695
And pretty much represented
my entire life's work. Heh.

16:39.599 --> 16:41.365
Of course, if uh...

16:41.401 --> 16:43.634
It were to mysteriously
reappear on my doorstep,

16:43.703 --> 16:45.269
Would I say anything
to anyone?

16:45.338 --> 16:47.572
Nope!
- Dad.

16:47.574 --> 16:49.073
- What?

16:49.208 --> 16:51.509
Well, I'm just saying,
I'm the type of person

16:51.578 --> 16:54.145
That likes to forgive...
And forget.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.081
I'm very forgiving.

16:58.351 --> 17:00.184
- (sighs)
you know, dad,

17:00.186 --> 17:02.720
Logan has been a huge help
with that wildie.

17:02.722 --> 17:05.723
He's helping me gentle it
for uh... Jessica.

17:05.792 --> 17:07.658
It's gonna be a shame
to see him go.

17:07.794 --> 17:09.527
- Where're you goin'?

17:10.864 --> 17:12.863
- Uh, my dad's comin' to pick
me up in a couple days.

17:12.899 --> 17:14.231
- Oh yeah? From where?

17:16.536 --> 17:18.302
- He's...He's been in jail,
actually.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.137
- (scoffs)

17:23.576 --> 17:25.343
Probably innocent though,
right?

17:25.478 --> 17:27.078
- Well...

17:27.213 --> 17:30.281
He made his mistakes,
but he served his time,

17:30.350 --> 17:33.217
And he's still my dad,
right?

17:33.219 --> 17:34.918
<i> Jack: He is at that.</i>

17:36.523 --> 17:38.489
And I hope your reunion is...

17:38.491 --> 17:40.324
Is a happy one.

17:40.326 --> 17:42.460
(utensils clang gently)

17:42.462 --> 17:46.163
♪♪♪

17:46.299 --> 17:47.898
(footsteps approach)

17:47.967 --> 17:49.433
- All right, I'm gonna head out
and take logan

17:49.502 --> 17:51.368
Back to the centre.
- Thanks so much for dinner.

17:51.404 --> 17:53.370
- It was our pleasure.

17:53.372 --> 17:55.372
- Bye.
- See you guys.

17:55.408 --> 17:57.441
(door opens and closes)

17:59.212 --> 18:01.645
- So, jack,
that watch of yours?

18:01.681 --> 18:03.647
I just can't stop
thinking about it.

18:03.683 --> 18:05.216
- Well, you should.
- Come on,

18:05.285 --> 18:07.318
What'd it look like?
What made it so special?

18:07.320 --> 18:09.987
- Parker, that watch
wasn't special, all right.

18:09.989 --> 18:11.255
(sponge splashes
in water)

18:11.390 --> 18:13.257
It was a piece of junk.

18:13.392 --> 18:15.526
(footsteps recede,
door opens and shuts)

18:17.130 --> 18:19.263
- It was gold
and it was engraved.

18:19.299 --> 18:22.033
- Engraved with what?
- J.E.B.

18:22.035 --> 18:24.202
Jefferson evans bartlett.

18:26.673 --> 18:28.406
(crickets chirp)

18:28.541 --> 18:35.345
♪♪♪

18:35.381 --> 18:37.814
(music turns sinister)

18:39.919 --> 18:42.153
(engine roars)

18:44.791 --> 18:46.757
(tires crunch in the gravel)

18:47.827 --> 18:49.560
(engine rumbling)

18:49.596 --> 18:53.497
(sombre music)

18:53.533 --> 18:56.099
(engine cuts out,
door opens)

18:56.136 --> 18:57.834
(door slams echoes)

18:57.871 --> 19:01.439
♪♪♪

19:01.574 --> 19:04.275
Dad? You all right?

19:04.410 --> 19:06.744
- Yeah, I'm all right.
What's it to you?

19:06.746 --> 19:08.246
- Think you should just
head inside.

19:08.381 --> 19:10.981
<i> - Don't tell me</i>
<i> what to do, boy!</i>

19:11.017 --> 19:13.517
Well, so, you're the boss
now, huh?

19:13.520 --> 19:16.987
Huh? Is that what
you're saying? Hmm? Is it?

19:17.056 --> 19:19.423
(hand slap)
mind your own business.

19:19.425 --> 19:21.392
(footsteps recede,
door shuts)

19:21.394 --> 19:23.527
♪♪♪

19:23.563 --> 19:25.862
(emotional exhale)

19:25.899 --> 19:29.833
♪♪♪

19:30.870 --> 19:32.203
(birds chirp)

19:33.940 --> 19:35.405
(doors creak shut)

19:37.476 --> 19:40.077
(footsteps thud)
oh, it's only you.

19:41.214 --> 19:42.613
- Thanks for that.

19:42.649 --> 19:44.548
What're you doing?

19:44.584 --> 19:46.951
- Searching local
classified listings

19:46.953 --> 19:48.686
For jack's watch.

19:48.755 --> 19:50.554
If someone has it,
they'll wanna sell it.

19:50.690 --> 19:53.224
Fast.
(keys clack)

19:53.226 --> 19:55.092
- You know, my trophy
was stolen.

19:55.094 --> 19:57.228
- Yes, I think
everyone's aware.

19:58.565 --> 20:00.698
- Well, maybe you can
search for it on there, too.

20:02.202 --> 20:03.900
Since it was a piece
of rodeo history.

20:05.438 --> 20:07.204
How 'bout this?

20:07.207 --> 20:09.707
You search for my trophy,
on that,

20:09.776 --> 20:11.608
And I'll be your boots
on the ground out there.

20:12.946 --> 20:14.578
You can't go answering
all those listings

20:14.614 --> 20:16.380
On your own, right?

20:16.515 --> 20:18.649
- Okay, then. It's a deal.

20:18.685 --> 20:20.851
- Excellent.
Do your thing.

20:20.987 --> 20:22.786
My advice is,
I would start with logan

20:22.822 --> 20:24.422
And his derelict friends.

20:24.424 --> 20:26.323
- There's no way
they did this.

20:28.027 --> 20:29.426
- Prove it.

20:30.597 --> 20:32.529
Rick: I think we need
to face facts.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.598
- (sighs) it's gone.

20:34.601 --> 20:36.901
What are we gonna do?

20:36.903 --> 20:38.602
- Crisis management.

20:38.604 --> 20:40.271
Luckily, it's my specialty.

20:40.406 --> 20:42.239
So, your laptop,

20:42.275 --> 20:43.941
Security level was
at its highest, right?

20:44.076 --> 20:45.909
And fingerprint protected?

20:47.747 --> 20:50.815
Okay, okay, but you did have
a password on it, correct?

20:50.817 --> 20:52.949
- Yes, yes. Absolutely,
I did.

20:53.086 --> 20:54.318
- Fantastic.

20:54.387 --> 20:55.886
And as long as it wasn't
something idiotic,

20:55.955 --> 20:58.555
Like 1234,
we're... We're fine.

20:58.591 --> 21:00.624
- And if it was...

21:00.693 --> 21:02.559
Something... Kinda like that?

21:02.695 --> 21:05.162
- Lou, do you not get how
many ultra-confidential

21:05.164 --> 21:06.997
Documents were on that thing?

21:07.000 --> 21:09.800
- Okay, now is probably
a good time to mention

21:09.802 --> 21:11.836
That there was something else

21:11.838 --> 21:14.305
On there, too... Something,

21:14.307 --> 21:16.373
Ahem, a little bit
more personal.

21:17.510 --> 21:19.443
It also had some photos
on there that were...

21:20.580 --> 21:22.580
Sort of inappropriate
for my children to see.

21:24.083 --> 21:26.249
(stressed exhale)
- whew, and uh...

21:26.286 --> 21:27.818
There they are.

21:28.888 --> 21:30.588
The uh...Whew...

21:30.723 --> 21:32.589
Chest pains. (exhales)

21:34.060 --> 21:36.193
Amy: So, any new developments
on the funding front?

21:36.329 --> 21:37.862
- I've got a few more
roads to go down.

21:37.997 --> 21:39.530
I'm not giving up hope
just yet.

21:39.532 --> 21:41.264
- Good. That's good.

21:41.301 --> 21:42.667
Hey, you ready
for our last day?

21:42.802 --> 21:44.401
- Absolutely, let's do it!

21:44.437 --> 21:46.504
- (chuckles)
hey, clint!

21:46.506 --> 21:48.372
Good to see you.
- Morning.

21:48.441 --> 21:50.007
(door slams)

21:50.142 --> 21:51.875
Glad I caught up
with you guys.

21:54.514 --> 21:56.413
Logan, I just got off
the phone

21:56.449 --> 21:58.281
With your case worker.

21:58.318 --> 22:00.351
<i> Your father didn't</i>
<i> make parole.</i>

22:00.486 --> 22:02.486
<i> He was denied. I'm sorry.</i>

22:02.555 --> 22:08.025
♪♪♪

22:08.027 --> 22:09.593
Amy: Logan, wait!

22:09.729 --> 22:12.162
♪♪♪

22:16.902 --> 22:18.769
Cooper, I'm not here
to criticize,

22:18.904 --> 22:20.637
I'm here to help.

22:20.707 --> 22:22.773
I put my name on the line for
the centre, too, you know.

22:22.809 --> 22:24.575
- Yeah, clint, I know,
all right.

22:24.577 --> 22:26.711
I know, I'm trying my best,
I just don't think I could--

22:27.914 --> 22:29.446
Hey.
- Hey.

22:29.482 --> 22:31.448
- Any luck? We've searched
all the buildings,

22:31.584 --> 22:33.317
Still no logan.
- Yeah, no,

22:33.386 --> 22:35.119
I searched the grounds, too.
- You know what?

22:35.121 --> 22:36.854
I'm gonna head over
to the group home.

22:36.923 --> 22:38.689
Maybe he'll show up there.

22:38.824 --> 22:40.491
(latch rattles,
gate creaks)

22:40.626 --> 22:42.593
- (sighs)

22:42.595 --> 22:44.462
(lock creaks)

22:46.665 --> 22:48.332
- So, what's going on
with you with you two?

22:48.401 --> 22:50.267
Is it all right?
- Yeah, it's fine.

22:50.269 --> 22:52.403
And uh...
If logan turns up,

22:52.405 --> 22:54.538
I'll give you a call.

22:54.574 --> 22:56.607
(tires crunch in the gravel)

22:56.742 --> 22:59.510
♪♪♪

22:59.512 --> 23:01.344
(keys clack)

23:03.282 --> 23:04.548
- (stressed sigh)

23:04.683 --> 23:07.184
- How's it going over there?
- Good, yeah.

23:07.253 --> 23:09.019
Not at all frustrating.

23:10.222 --> 23:11.822
- Searching online
classifieds

23:11.858 --> 23:13.757
Is all about using keywords.

23:13.892 --> 23:17.360
I've tried things like
"antique" "engraved".

23:17.397 --> 23:20.164
- Well, how 'bout
"trophy, iconic, legend"?

23:20.166 --> 23:21.565
"missing, get back."

23:21.601 --> 23:23.366
Also, "collector's item."

23:23.403 --> 23:25.135
- You know there
isn't much resale value

23:25.138 --> 23:27.738
On stolen trophies, right?
It's like stolen art -

23:27.873 --> 23:29.706
Too high profile.

23:29.776 --> 23:31.709
But a random old watch?

23:31.844 --> 23:33.310
That's sellable.

23:34.380 --> 23:36.380
- Well, aren't you
a little ray of hope.

23:36.449 --> 23:38.181
(sighs)

23:39.652 --> 23:42.653
- I've got nothing.
Zero listings.

23:42.655 --> 23:44.387
- Well, I keep tellin' ya,

23:44.424 --> 23:46.590
This isn't just
about jack's watch.

23:48.194 --> 23:49.860
- You're right!

23:49.896 --> 23:52.195
I need to examine
all the robberies.

23:52.231 --> 23:53.730
I need to go bigger!

23:53.800 --> 23:56.399
- Yes! Go big or go home.

23:56.436 --> 23:58.235
You still have a home, right?

24:03.843 --> 24:05.809
(hooves thud)

24:05.845 --> 24:07.544
- Hey.
- (shadow nickers)

24:07.680 --> 24:10.147
- Looks like it's just
you and me today, okay?

24:11.984 --> 24:14.318
I know.

24:14.320 --> 24:15.919
(dirt crunches under tires)

24:15.988 --> 24:17.554
Hey, you're here!

24:19.058 --> 24:20.691
- Yeah.

24:20.826 --> 24:22.493
But uh...

24:22.495 --> 24:24.695
I came to say goodbye.

24:24.697 --> 24:26.563
- Where are you going?

24:26.599 --> 24:28.599
- I don't know yet,
but I'm going.

24:28.734 --> 24:30.901
You know, I need that
blank state start.

24:32.338 --> 24:33.837
I'm not gonna let my dad
and his dumb mistakes

24:33.906 --> 24:36.040
Hold me back anymore.
I'm better off on my own.

24:37.910 --> 24:40.244
- Logan, I know things
seem bad right now,

24:40.246 --> 24:41.712
But...

24:41.847 --> 24:44.848
Running away isn't gonna fix
anything.

24:44.884 --> 24:46.250
- (shadow nickers)
- right, shadow?

24:46.252 --> 24:47.584
(hooves thud,
shadow nickers)

24:47.620 --> 24:49.920
- Hey, boy.

24:50.055 --> 24:52.056
(nickers)
- (small laugh)

24:53.259 --> 24:55.259
♪♪♪

24:55.261 --> 24:56.994
- I uh, I gotta go.

24:57.129 --> 24:59.596
(clip snaps)
I'm sorry.

25:03.970 --> 25:07.804
♪♪♪

25:07.806 --> 25:11.075
(fire crackles,
poker clangs)

25:12.712 --> 25:16.479
♪♪♪

25:16.516 --> 25:19.750
- (jack sighs)

25:19.752 --> 25:22.219
Lyndy get to bed all right?
- Yeah. Yeah,

25:22.354 --> 25:24.021
Once I told her
that her gg put

25:24.090 --> 25:26.190
Extra strong locks
on all the doors.

25:26.325 --> 25:27.924
- (chuckles)

25:27.960 --> 25:29.894
- (sighs)

25:30.029 --> 25:32.563
So, logan's dad
didn't make parole.

25:32.565 --> 25:34.264
- I'm sorry to hear that.

25:36.569 --> 25:38.035
- But logan is...

25:38.104 --> 25:40.237
Still leaving.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.406
I don't know where he's going

25:42.475 --> 25:44.241
Or what will happen to him.

25:45.778 --> 25:48.378
He's just a kid, you know.

25:50.016 --> 25:52.716
He has such great instincts
with horses.

25:54.053 --> 25:55.719
I... Feel like,

25:56.789 --> 25:58.589
I feel like I failed him.

25:58.591 --> 25:59.656
I was hoping that...

26:00.793 --> 26:02.259
I could help him with that,
you know,

26:02.394 --> 26:04.728
That... That he'd want to.

26:04.863 --> 26:07.731
- Oh, he probably did.
No doubt he's upset.

26:09.835 --> 26:11.936
- Yeah, he's angry.

26:12.071 --> 26:13.871
He's furious at his dad.

26:14.006 --> 26:16.373
- Yeah.

26:16.442 --> 26:19.442
Father and son relationships,
they...

26:22.281 --> 26:24.548
They can be tough.

26:24.617 --> 26:25.883
And fragile.

26:29.021 --> 26:32.756
As a kid, you,
you look up to your dad,

26:32.825 --> 26:36.226
And you do your very best
to be just like him.

26:39.231 --> 26:41.031
And then,
when they trip up,

26:41.067 --> 26:42.833
Well, that's when you realize
your dad

26:42.835 --> 26:45.836
Isn't the hero
you thought he was.

26:45.838 --> 26:47.470
He's just a...

26:49.041 --> 26:50.573
A person.

26:53.346 --> 26:56.446
It's not on you
to fix what's broken

26:56.482 --> 26:58.581
Between logan and his dad.

26:59.985 --> 27:02.485
All you can do is be here,
and you are.

27:04.857 --> 27:06.523
- Yeah.

27:07.860 --> 27:09.592
Thank you.

27:10.663 --> 27:12.829
I'm gonna head to bed.

27:13.966 --> 27:16.733
(stressed exhale)
- sleep well.

27:18.204 --> 27:19.736
(fire crackles)
(sharp exhale)

27:23.409 --> 27:25.342
(sighs)

27:25.477 --> 27:27.510
(poker clangs)

27:27.546 --> 27:29.946
(clanging echoes, whoosh)

27:32.084 --> 27:35.485
♪♪♪

27:35.521 --> 27:37.387
(fire crackles)

27:38.891 --> 27:40.757
(door closes)

27:42.361 --> 27:44.495
We gotta move that herd
tomorrow, dad.

27:44.630 --> 27:46.296
I can't miss another rodeo.

27:46.365 --> 27:47.897
<i> Jefferson: (chuckles)</i>

27:47.933 --> 27:49.766
<i> Rodeos.</i>

27:49.902 --> 27:53.704
<i> This ranch is more important</i>
<i> than any damn rodeo.</i>

27:53.706 --> 27:55.439
- I know,

27:55.441 --> 27:56.774
So help me get it done.

27:56.909 --> 27:59.610
- You think you know
what's best for this place?

27:59.612 --> 28:01.745
<i> Prove it!</i>

28:01.880 --> 28:04.647
♪♪♪

28:04.684 --> 28:06.850
Happy birthday.
- (watch jingles)

28:08.020 --> 28:10.187
(door closes)
- I don't want it.

28:11.257 --> 28:13.957
I don't want anything
from you!

28:13.959 --> 28:20.396
♪♪♪

28:22.134 --> 28:24.901
<i> Lyndy: Mama! Mama!</i>

28:24.970 --> 28:27.070
- Oh, sweetie,
are you okay?

28:27.106 --> 28:29.139
- What's wrong?
What happened?

28:29.175 --> 28:31.541
- Someone's at the door.
I hear scratching.

28:33.279 --> 28:34.878
- No, no, honey.
It's okay.

28:34.914 --> 28:37.280
It was just a bad dream,
right?

28:37.316 --> 28:39.349
You're fine.

28:39.418 --> 28:41.551
(footsteps crunch)

28:41.587 --> 28:43.487
♪♪♪

28:43.489 --> 28:45.588
<i> Jefferson: You think you know</i>
<i> what's best for this place?</i>

28:46.658 --> 28:48.092
<i> Prove it!</i>

28:48.227 --> 28:51.828
♪♪♪

28:56.736 --> 28:58.234
I think
I found something.

28:59.405 --> 29:01.070
These x's are all
the robberies reported

29:01.107 --> 29:02.939
Within the area.

29:04.009 --> 29:05.943
The thief moves around.

29:05.945 --> 29:08.278
One town is hit,
then another, and another!

29:08.314 --> 29:09.813
- Yeah, well,
they're gonna move around

29:09.882 --> 29:11.714
'cause they don't wanna
get caught.

29:11.751 --> 29:13.183
- But the moves aren't
random.

29:13.318 --> 29:14.952
I think I found a pattern.

29:14.954 --> 29:16.753
- Whadda ya mean?

29:16.789 --> 29:18.588
- The robberies
match another thing

29:18.657 --> 29:19.923
That's been moving
through the area.

29:21.327 --> 29:23.059
The fair!

29:23.061 --> 29:25.595
The fair sets up,
robberies are reported,

29:25.631 --> 29:27.530
The fair moves on,

29:27.566 --> 29:29.332
Reports stop.
- Hmm.

29:29.368 --> 29:31.201
- I bet our thief
works at the fair!

29:31.237 --> 29:34.137
- I don't know. I mean, the
timeline adds up, but...

29:34.140 --> 29:37.074
It also matches when
logan and his crew

29:37.209 --> 29:38.741
Arrived at coopers.

29:38.778 --> 29:40.711
(keys clack)

29:40.713 --> 29:42.546
- That's where the fair
was set up in hudson.

29:43.649 --> 29:44.882
And look,

29:45.017 --> 29:47.617
There's a pawn shop
under a mile away!

29:47.619 --> 29:49.353
Come on, how do you feel

29:49.355 --> 29:51.288
About getting those boots
on the ground?

29:51.423 --> 29:52.956
- (chuckles)

29:55.461 --> 29:57.694
(drill whirs)

29:57.730 --> 29:59.229
- Jack!

29:59.265 --> 30:02.098
Jack bartlett!
What are you doing?

30:02.100 --> 30:04.167
- I'm protecting
my great-grandchildren.

30:04.170 --> 30:05.869
What does it look like?

30:05.938 --> 30:07.871
- No, you're not
protecting them, honey,

30:08.006 --> 30:10.306
You are now terrifying them.
I know you feel responsible

30:10.342 --> 30:11.908
For the burglary,
but it was days ago.

30:11.944 --> 30:15.078
We're safe. We're fine.
Get over your guilt.

30:15.147 --> 30:17.247
- It's not guilt, all right.

30:17.283 --> 30:20.183
- Well then, what is it?
- It's that damn watch!

30:20.186 --> 30:21.852
(footsteps crunch)

30:24.089 --> 30:26.122
<i> Rick: Okay, I've spoken</i>
<i> to our tech guys,</i>

30:26.158 --> 30:28.491
<i> They can wipe your</i>
<i> laptop remotely.</i>

30:28.561 --> 30:30.326
- Just make the call.

30:30.362 --> 30:32.262
(beeps phone on)
- (stressed sigh)

30:32.298 --> 30:34.197
- Hey, yeah um...

30:34.200 --> 30:35.933
Wipe it.

30:36.068 --> 30:37.934
- (sighs)
- mm-hmm.

30:39.271 --> 30:41.404
It's done.
- Oh, thank god.

30:42.474 --> 30:44.807
(sighs)
- uh...

30:44.844 --> 30:46.643
♪♪♪

30:46.778 --> 30:48.678
- You have my laptop.

30:48.747 --> 30:50.080
Why do you have my laptop?

30:50.082 --> 30:51.848
- Came in the other night,

30:51.851 --> 30:53.617
And it was just sitting on
your desk.

30:53.619 --> 30:55.418
Didn't seem very safe.
I mean...

30:55.454 --> 30:57.253
Don't you know about
the robberies in town?

30:59.024 --> 31:00.891
I locked it up
in the supply closet.

31:01.026 --> 31:03.760
- That was three days ago.
I thought it was stolen.

31:03.796 --> 31:05.962
- Well, I left you a note,
telling you where it was.

31:05.998 --> 31:07.830
I put it on your...

31:11.303 --> 31:13.437
Wow, how do you
get anything done?

31:13.572 --> 31:15.605
(scoffs)
(footsteps recede)

31:15.674 --> 31:17.707
- Wh-

31:17.709 --> 31:20.644
♪♪♪

31:20.646 --> 31:23.914
(the paint neighs)

31:23.916 --> 31:26.249
- Hey, come here, boy.
(clicks tongue)

31:26.318 --> 31:28.318
(the paint nickers)

31:28.320 --> 31:30.053
(hooves thud gently)

31:31.323 --> 31:33.122
- Hey.
- Hi.

31:33.158 --> 31:35.325
(grass rustles, hooves thud)

31:36.528 --> 31:38.428
- You stayed. I'm glad.

31:38.497 --> 31:40.430
- I figured, you know,

31:40.432 --> 31:42.732
I can go whenever, but...

31:42.801 --> 31:45.001
I mean, you said the horse
needs to trust us, right.

31:45.037 --> 31:47.603
So, I didn't really wanna
give him abandonment issues.

31:47.640 --> 31:48.972
- That makes sense.

31:50.175 --> 31:51.841
- But the truth is...

31:51.911 --> 31:53.876
I got on the road,
and I just...

31:55.614 --> 31:57.213
I don't know,
I didn't wanna be there.

32:00.286 --> 32:02.285
- Come on. Let's get to work.

32:02.288 --> 32:04.287
(the paint nickers)

32:05.357 --> 32:06.923
- (clicks tongue)

32:06.959 --> 32:08.558
Come on, let's go.

32:08.560 --> 32:10.427
Hup, hup, hup, hup!

32:10.496 --> 32:12.195
(hooves thud)

32:13.732 --> 32:15.432
- Come on!
Hup, hup, hup, hup!

32:15.567 --> 32:17.234
(the paint snorts)

32:17.369 --> 32:19.536
<i> Good boy.</i>

32:19.671 --> 32:21.838
That's it.

32:21.840 --> 32:23.306
(the paint neighs)
good job, logan!

32:23.375 --> 32:25.742
Get him up! Get him up!
Hup! Hup! Hup! Hup!

32:25.811 --> 32:27.510
(the paint snorts)

32:28.547 --> 32:30.113
(amy chuckles)

32:31.216 --> 32:33.249
Look at him go!

32:33.319 --> 32:35.318
Good boy.

32:35.387 --> 32:38.788
♪♪♪

32:38.824 --> 32:40.557
Good boy.

32:40.559 --> 32:43.393
♪♪♪

32:43.528 --> 32:45.128
(the paint snorts)

32:45.197 --> 32:47.597
♪♪♪

32:47.666 --> 32:50.333
Logan: Hey, buddy. Hey.

32:50.468 --> 32:52.268
(chuckles softly)

32:52.338 --> 32:54.204
(amy chuckles softly)

32:54.339 --> 32:57.273
♪♪♪

32:59.345 --> 33:01.344
Jack: We all know
there was no love lost

33:01.347 --> 33:03.212
Between my dad and me,

33:03.248 --> 33:06.149
But losing that watch...
It mattered.

33:07.219 --> 33:09.019
For whatever reason,

33:09.088 --> 33:11.488
It brought back memories
and...

33:11.557 --> 33:13.156
- Which ones?

33:13.291 --> 33:15.092
- The kind I'd rather forget.

33:16.462 --> 33:18.227
From after my sister's death.

33:18.263 --> 33:20.096
When it was just me and...

33:20.232 --> 33:22.032
And my dad, here,

33:22.167 --> 33:25.368
And I was workin' my tail off
to keep this place afloat

33:25.437 --> 33:28.839
While he was drowning himself
in grief and alcohol.

33:28.974 --> 33:31.307
- Why wouldn't you just tell
me why you were upset, honey?

33:31.343 --> 33:33.376
- I'm not upset!

33:33.412 --> 33:35.378
I'm not upset
about the watch,

33:35.381 --> 33:37.180
Or the break-in,
what I am, is angry.

33:38.317 --> 33:40.783
I'm angry at what it all
conjured up, that...

33:40.819 --> 33:42.652
You know, that feeling...

33:43.789 --> 33:46.456
That you can't even be safe
in your own home.

33:48.594 --> 33:50.861
I haven't felt that way
since June died, and...

33:52.765 --> 33:55.398
And dad, he took that one
out on me.

33:58.203 --> 34:01.338
- What your dad did
is heartbreaking,

34:01.473 --> 34:03.806
But you can't be angry
at yourself.

34:03.842 --> 34:05.341
- Why not?

34:05.377 --> 34:07.343
I didn't make you feel safe,

34:07.379 --> 34:09.413
I made you feel
the way he made me feel,

34:09.548 --> 34:11.681
And I promised I would
never do that to anyone.

34:11.750 --> 34:13.183
- No!

34:13.252 --> 34:15.819
You always make me feel safe.

34:15.954 --> 34:18.221
Okay? You're not your father.

34:20.492 --> 34:22.358
(sighs) you need to pull
yourself out of the past,

34:22.394 --> 34:24.227
And focus on the present.

34:24.296 --> 34:26.929
And take your
great-granddaughter fishing.

34:27.966 --> 34:29.466
- Okay.

34:29.468 --> 34:32.002
- Appreciate all that
you have.

34:32.004 --> 34:33.870
Because you made this!

34:35.007 --> 34:37.907
You pulled yourself
out of a very dark place

34:37.943 --> 34:40.376
And you created this...

34:41.646 --> 34:44.380
Beautiful, perfect,

34:44.382 --> 34:46.583
Safe home for us.

34:48.987 --> 34:50.387
Okay?

34:50.522 --> 34:53.189
♪♪♪

34:54.993 --> 34:56.393
(footsteps thud)

34:56.528 --> 34:58.128
(inquisitive music)

34:58.263 --> 35:05.268
♪♪♪

35:05.270 --> 35:08.037
♪♪♪

35:08.107 --> 35:10.006
- I'd like to see this watch,
please.

35:12.644 --> 35:14.411
(glass rasps)

35:16.982 --> 35:20.684
♪♪♪

35:20.819 --> 35:22.586
Tim: That it?
- (watch rattles)

35:23.955 --> 35:26.055
All right, buddy,

35:26.125 --> 35:28.158
We all know where this
watch came from

35:28.293 --> 35:30.227
And I'm sure if I look around
there's a few other

35:30.362 --> 35:32.762
Hot little items in here,
if I take a good look.

35:32.764 --> 35:35.031
- No clue what you mean.
Sorry.

35:35.100 --> 35:38.068
- All right, let me make myself
a little clearer.

35:38.070 --> 35:40.303
What--

35:41.507 --> 35:43.506
- Hey! You can't do that!

35:43.575 --> 35:45.242
(trophy rattles)

35:45.377 --> 35:47.711
- Whoa, wh-hoa!

35:47.846 --> 35:50.513
♪♪♪

35:50.516 --> 35:53.049
See this? Tim fleming.

35:53.051 --> 35:55.151
Tim fleming.
Nice to meet ya.

35:55.154 --> 35:56.853
Okay, here's what's gonna
happen.

35:56.988 --> 35:59.022
We're gonna take that watch
and this trophy,

35:59.091 --> 36:00.524
And we're gonna leave,

36:00.659 --> 36:02.392
And you're not gonna say
a thing about it.

36:02.394 --> 36:03.993
Come on, partner.

36:04.062 --> 36:06.629
- Wait, I need to know.
Who brought these in?

36:06.698 --> 36:08.731
What did they look like?

36:08.767 --> 36:10.266
- It was kids, right?

36:10.335 --> 36:13.069
- Uh... It was...
An older guy.

36:13.105 --> 36:16.439
Bunch of tattoos...
Definitely not a local.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.209
- And definitely not logan.
- (scoffs)

36:21.880 --> 36:24.214
- So, are you gonna
call the cops?

36:24.216 --> 36:26.082
- Oh, absolutely.

36:26.084 --> 36:29.219
♪♪♪

36:29.354 --> 36:31.087
Amy: We did some great work
today.

36:31.223 --> 36:33.155
- Yeah? And that wildie
came a long way, huh?

36:33.192 --> 36:34.357
- Yeah.

36:34.492 --> 36:36.292
- You think he'll be ready
to ride soon?

36:36.328 --> 36:38.861
- Yeah, soon,
if we keep this up.

36:38.931 --> 36:40.863
I just realized, I've never
seen you on a horse.

36:40.933 --> 36:43.766
Can you ride?
- Uh, I mean, probably not.

36:43.802 --> 36:46.502
I've never tried it.
- No? All right.

36:46.538 --> 36:48.905
You want a lesson?

36:48.974 --> 36:50.573
Both: (chuckle)

36:50.642 --> 36:52.609
- Come on!
- All right.

36:54.213 --> 36:56.512
All right, so sit up nice
and tall in the saddle,

36:56.548 --> 36:58.481
Make sure you look
where you wanna go.

36:58.550 --> 37:00.784
Okay, now I want you
to steer.

37:00.786 --> 37:02.952
(hooves thud)

37:02.988 --> 37:04.988
<i> That's it.</i>

37:04.990 --> 37:07.824
♪♪♪

37:07.959 --> 37:09.659
(hooves thud,
shadow nickers)

37:09.661 --> 37:12.895
♪♪♪

37:12.965 --> 37:15.197
Okay, okay, okay, that's it.
That's it. Slow down.

37:15.234 --> 37:16.933
<i> Slow down. We don't need</i>
<i> to be going that fast!</i>

37:17.068 --> 37:18.802
<i> - Don't worry.</i>
<i> - (shadow nickers)</i>

37:18.804 --> 37:20.803
- All right!

37:20.839 --> 37:22.939
(hooves thud)

37:23.074 --> 37:29.946
♪♪♪

37:30.081 --> 37:35.952
♪♪♪

37:39.958 --> 37:41.624
(birds chirp)

37:41.627 --> 37:44.126
(rod rattles gently)

37:45.931 --> 37:47.397
(reel cranks)

37:47.532 --> 37:49.799
Jack: Yeah. Right there.
See that?

37:51.603 --> 37:53.436
(line zips)

37:53.571 --> 37:55.438
- Yeah, and your reel there.
- Okay.

37:55.474 --> 37:57.374
- Start reeling.
- (reel cranks)

37:59.844 --> 38:01.244
There.

38:01.379 --> 38:02.712
- There you go.

38:02.748 --> 38:06.115
(reel cranks)
see? Just like that.

38:07.185 --> 38:10.119
- There! That's it!

38:10.121 --> 38:12.956
<i> Old jack: You're doing great,</i>
<i> kiddo.</i>

38:13.091 --> 38:15.257
(reel cranking)

38:15.294 --> 38:17.026
<i> Jefferson: You're doing</i>
<i> great, jack.</i>

38:17.095 --> 38:18.662
<i> I'm proud of you.</i>

38:18.797 --> 38:20.997
♪♪♪

38:21.132 --> 38:23.666
(reel cranks)
- I'm proud of you.

38:23.735 --> 38:29.271
♪♪♪

38:33.745 --> 38:37.013
♪♪♪

38:37.015 --> 38:38.948
- All right!
Is everybody ready?

38:39.017 --> 38:40.350
- (trophy thuds on table)

38:42.454 --> 38:45.088
Amy: Oh! That's awesome, dad.
(clapping)

38:45.090 --> 38:47.156
- Well, at least one of us
got a happy ending.

38:47.192 --> 38:50.026
- And aren't we glad
it was tim.

38:50.028 --> 38:53.162
- (chuckling)
- I'd like to propose a toast

38:53.231 --> 38:54.731
To... Parker.

38:54.733 --> 38:56.900
For your expert detective work.

38:57.035 --> 38:59.102
Parker, you and I
make a great team.

38:59.104 --> 39:01.504
- Actually, you made a good
sidekick.

39:01.540 --> 39:04.274
All: (laugh)

39:04.409 --> 39:06.642
- Well, the chief of police
sends his thanks, too.

39:06.712 --> 39:08.644
- Can I add something?

39:08.680 --> 39:11.914
Parker, thank you for
saving the centre's rep

39:11.950 --> 39:13.683
And taking the heat
off my friends.

39:13.818 --> 39:15.451
And off me.

39:15.487 --> 39:17.720
- It was my honour.
All: (chuckle)

39:17.789 --> 39:19.289
Jack: I'm just glad
to see you back

39:19.424 --> 39:20.657
At our table tonight, logan,

39:20.792 --> 39:23.359
And know that you're always
welcome here.

39:23.362 --> 39:25.428
- I'll cheers to that.

39:27.466 --> 39:30.032
All: Cheers!
(glasses clink)

39:31.370 --> 39:33.869
♪♪♪

39:33.905 --> 39:36.338
(door clunks open)

39:38.810 --> 39:40.543
(door squeaks shut)

39:40.678 --> 39:43.012
(footsteps shuffle)

39:43.048 --> 39:44.547
- Logan, I just wanna say...

39:47.619 --> 39:49.953
Your dad might've made
a few bad choices

39:50.088 --> 39:52.822
To wind up where he is but...

39:52.858 --> 39:54.891
That doesn't mean
he's a bad man.

39:56.161 --> 39:58.628
Now, I know you're angry
at him,

39:58.630 --> 40:01.698
But don't carry it with ya,
trust me.

40:01.833 --> 40:03.433
It's...

40:03.435 --> 40:05.501
(soft chuckle)

40:05.637 --> 40:07.437
It's not worth it.

40:07.572 --> 40:12.742
♪♪♪

40:12.877 --> 40:14.911
<i> (tires rumble on gravel)</i>

40:18.116 --> 40:20.316
(seatbelts unclicks)

40:20.318 --> 40:22.751
(doors open and shut)

40:24.656 --> 40:26.989
- So, we'll get back
to work later this week?

40:27.025 --> 40:29.058
- Yep. Sounds great.

40:29.127 --> 40:30.926
(bike rattles)

40:30.962 --> 40:33.263
And uh, amy, uh...

40:33.398 --> 40:34.864
Thank you.

40:34.999 --> 40:38.000
You know, this is all...
Just making me feel

40:38.036 --> 40:40.069
Like I actually
belong somewhere, you know.

40:41.339 --> 40:42.806
Haven't felt like that
in a long time.

40:44.910 --> 40:46.609
See ya.
(bike gears click)

40:48.813 --> 40:50.313
- Clint!

40:50.315 --> 40:51.814
Hey, what are you
doin' here?

40:51.850 --> 40:53.950
- Well, cooper's gone,
he left.

40:54.019 --> 40:55.751
- What do you mean, he left?

40:55.787 --> 40:57.620
- He threatened to do it
the other day,

40:57.689 --> 41:00.623
And I thought I talked some
reason into him but...

41:00.692 --> 41:03.393
Amy, this centre is so far
in the hole,

41:03.395 --> 41:05.528
I think he just got
overwhelmed.

41:05.663 --> 41:07.964
I think he just needed
to walk away.

41:08.099 --> 41:11.100
- What about the horses?
Logan? The kids?

41:12.604 --> 41:14.737
- Well, I'm gonna step in.

41:14.739 --> 41:16.639
Temporarily. Um...

41:18.210 --> 41:19.642
♪♪♪

41:19.777 --> 41:22.311
Amy, if cooper
doesn't come back,

41:23.949 --> 41:26.315
I think this centre's
gonna have to shut down.

41:26.351 --> 41:30.653
♪♪♪

41:33.758 --> 41:36.325
- So, I told logan
to forgive his dad.

41:37.496 --> 41:39.062
- I know. I heard.

41:40.899 --> 41:43.265
You gonna be able
to do the same?

41:43.301 --> 41:44.600
- Oh, I don't know.

41:45.637 --> 41:47.803
I'm workin' on it.

41:47.839 --> 41:50.440
♪♪♪

41:50.442 --> 41:52.809
You know, down at that pond,
with lyndy...

41:53.979 --> 41:56.178
I remembered a time
when it was good.

41:58.450 --> 42:01.551
When I was still
so in awe of him.

42:04.322 --> 42:06.890
But then, life dealt us
the hand it did.

42:08.593 --> 42:11.627
I realized my dad
did one thing right.

42:11.763 --> 42:13.663
He made me put this ranch,

42:14.866 --> 42:16.566
This place,

42:16.701 --> 42:18.635
Above everything else,

42:18.770 --> 42:21.103
And I am grateful for that.

42:21.139 --> 42:22.738
- I am, too.

42:24.776 --> 42:26.709
And I'm grateful for you.

42:27.812 --> 42:30.046
(small chuckle,
glasses clink)

42:31.683 --> 42:33.449
(door clunks open, shuts)

42:33.451 --> 42:34.750
- Hi, honey.

42:36.021 --> 42:37.787
- Jack, I wanted you to know.

42:37.789 --> 42:40.056
The trophy wasn't the only
thing tim and I found today.

42:44.496 --> 42:46.195
Lisa: (gasps)

42:46.231 --> 42:48.397
♪♪♪

42:48.433 --> 42:50.265
(glass clinks on table)

42:52.337 --> 42:54.470
- I don't believe it.

42:54.472 --> 42:56.005
Thank you, parker.

42:56.140 --> 42:57.740
- (giggles)

42:57.809 --> 43:00.343
♪♪♪

43:00.345 --> 43:02.412
- I'll wear it right now.

43:02.547 --> 43:09.452
♪♪♪

43:09.521 --> 43:14.757
♪♪♪

43:16.828 --> 43:23.899
♪♪♪

43:23.901 --> 43:31.006
♪♪♪

43:33.444 --> 43:35.277
(door squeaks open, shuts)

43:35.313 --> 43:37.446
♪♪♪

43:41.519 --> 43:48.524
♪♪♪

43:48.526 --> 43:55.464
♪♪♪

43:55.533 --> 44:02.504
♪♪♪
